"admin area. After activation, the <em>Plugins &gt; Editor</em> and "
"<em>Appearance &gt; Theme Editor</em> menu items disappear from the admin "
"menu and are not accessible via direct URL. This feature works by setting "
"the <code>DISALLOW_FILE_EDIT</code> WordPress constant. This is a "
"recommended security measure as it prevents direct browser-based editing of "
"server files in case of compromised administrator accounts."
